Subject: (cherry-pick-branch-heads/7559) Fix potential crash when using
 encoder speed controller.
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The list of speed controllers needs to be reset when we release the
encoder - otherwise we end up appending more of them to the list. In
some cases this may lead to a crash.

Merge note: The _more_configs bots are all failing with the same error
message. "tools.mb.mb.MBErr: Phase cxx23 doesn't exist for
win_x86_more_configs on tryserver.webrtc". Looks like the bot config
for the branch isn't working properly. Since all other bots pass,
setting No-Try.

(cherry picked from commit 7379b40231e0ffe92a8aad931438c22729080b1f)

